<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="236" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,151,647]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,439,295,320]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">Diagnostic features.</emphasis>
Frons yellow with V-shaped black mark near base of antennae; antennae completely black (
<figureCitation box="[231,319,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="36.[151,249,1965,1987]" captionTargetBox="[174,1401,196,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[172,1404,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 23. Platypygus turkmenorum male paratype: a — head (anterior view), b — mesonotum (dorsal view), c — wing, d — adult habit (lateral view). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248571/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">
Fig. 
<number box="[288,319,332,356]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
a); postgena normal without posterior extension; occiput black, upper part of occiput with long yellowish hairs (
<figureCitation box="[347,434,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="36.[151,249,1965,1987]" captionTargetBox="[174,1401,196,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[172,1404,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 23. Platypygus turkmenorum male paratype: a — head (anterior view), b — mesonotum (dorsal view), c — wing, d — adult habit (lateral view). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248571/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">
Fig. 
<number box="[404,434,367,392]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
d); mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[626,712,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="36.[151,249,1965,1987]" captionTargetBox="[174,1401,196,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[172,1404,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 23. Platypygus turkmenorum male paratype: a — head (anterior view), b — mesonotum (dorsal view), c — wing, d — adult habit (lateral view). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248571/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">
Fig. 
<number box="[683,712,367,392]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
b) minutely hairy, yellow with large contiguous black pattern medially, mark extending anteriorly as stripe to anterior margin of mesonotum; postpronotal lobes and postalar calli yellow; lateral margins of mesonotum yellow; lateral black spot next to transverse suture coalesced with median pattern; black prescutellar area with large yellow oval spot; scutellum completely yellow; halter yellow; costa ends slightly beyond vein R 
<number box="[528,536,526,540]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[545,552,526,540]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236" value="5.0">5</number>
; crossvein r-m at middle of cell dm (
<figureCitation box="[967,1051,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="36.[151,249,1965,1987]" captionTargetBox="[174,1401,196,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[172,1404,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 23. Platypygus turkmenorum male paratype: a — head (anterior view), b — mesonotum (dorsal view), c — wing, d — adult habit (lateral view). Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248571/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">
Fig. 
<number box="[1020,1051,512,536]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
c); legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,151,647]" box="[199,1397,550,576]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,369,550,575]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Due to the paucity of available specimens, we did not dissect the male 
<typeStatus box="[1176,1272,552,576]" pageId="37" pageNumber="236">paratype</typeStatus>
in ZMHB.
</paragraph>
